==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anthracene
<hw>An"thra*cene</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'a`nqrax</grk> coal.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A solid
hydrocarbon, <chform>C6H4.C2H2.C6H4</chform>, which accompanies
naphthalene in the last stages of the distillation of coal tar. Its
chief use is in the artificial production of alizarin.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>anthracin</asp>.]</altsp><-- tricyclic
aromatic hydrocarbon. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anthracene oil</ent>⟦br⟧
